line_1: All tangled as it wound through brake and briar:
line_2: A thousand shapeless forms of terror dire,

line_1: All tangled as it wound through brake and briar:
line_2: Here shrieks the ill-omened bird, there glares the meteor's fire.

line_1: I lightly leap o'er brook, or briar,
line_2: And step — as far as I desire.
